WEST NILE VIRUS UPDATE 2008 - WESTERN HEMISPHERE (11)
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 16 Jul 2008
From: Tom Yuill, ProMED-mail Viral Diseases Moderator <promed@promedmail.org>


Because West Nile virus (WNV) has become endemic in North America and cases
can be expected to occur throughout the virus transmission season,
ProMED-mail will be reporting only newly detected virus and human cases in
US states and Canadian provinces for the current reporting period. Those
wishing to see the complete summary for virus detection in birds,
mosquitoes, sentinel animals, and equines as well as a breakdown of human
disease cases for 2008 can access that information on the following sites:

Canada:
Public Health Agency of Canada (PHAC)
<http://www.phac-aspc.gc.ca/wnv-vwn/mon-hmnsurv-eng.php>
Canadian Cooperative Wildlife Health Centre (The URL for the provincial
maps of West Nile virus detection in birds is not yet available, but PHAC
bird data can be accessed at):
<http://www.cnphi-wnv.ca/healthnet/Mainpage.do>.

USA:
US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), Division of
Vector-Borne Infectious Diseases, West Nile virus human cases:
<http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/dvbid/westnile/surv&controlCaseCount08_detailed.htm>

Centers for Disease Control, Division of Vector-Borne Infectious Diseases
and Geological Survey West Nile virus maps:
<http://diseasemaps.usgs.gov/index.html>.

Canada
------
Date: 28 Jun-5 Jul 2008: no WNV human cases
Date: 1 Apr-16 Jul 2008: no virus detected in birds reported.

USA
---
Date: 8-15 Jul 2008
States newly reporting WNV detected: Arkansas, Missouri, Pennsylvania, West
Virginia
States newly reporting new human cases: Alabama, Arkansas. Total human
cases for 2008: 28 with no fatalities.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
